The paper deals with security vulnerabilities and exploits in computer programs, which suggests that it belongs to the category of Computer Security and Cryptography (cs.CR). However, the paper also discusses programming languages theory and secure compilation, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also touches on system design and behavior, which suggests that it could belong to the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the compositionality of exploits in a compiler stack, which suggests that it could belong to the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO).
